init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: News such as a plane crash is more exciting than the president announcing tax cuts or a new way to help homeless children.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I feel that not being informed is better than reading a bunch of news that may make you feel down and frustrated.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: If you know about a lot of the negative things going on in the world,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is really up to the person to take whatever information they learn from the media and apply it to their lifestyle however they want.
